# fdtd-apml — PolyBench/C Kernel (Baseline & PIM Variant)

**Workload:** Finite-Difference Time-Domain with Anisotropic Perfectly Matched Layer (FDTD-APML).

## Benchmark Source

```
* * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
* PolyBench/C 4.2.1 (beta)  *
* * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
```
Copyright (c) 2011–2016 The Ohio State University.

Contact (for original code):  
- Louis-Noel Pouchet <pouchet@cse.ohio-state.edu>  
- Tomofumi Yuki <tomofumi.yuki@inria.fr>

---

## Build

Run:

```bash
make
```

This produces two executables:

- `fdtd-apml_baseline.exe` — baseline code  
- `fdtd-apml_pim.exe` — modified PIM code

> Tip: You can override the compiler if needed, e.g.:
> ```bash
> make CC=gcc-15
> ```

---

## Dataset Selection

Dataset size/type can be changed using the flags within the corresponding header file (e.g., `fdtd-apml.h`).

---

## Run

```bash
./fdtd-apml_baseline.exe
./fdtd-apml_pim.exe
```

---

## PIM Output

The PIM variant (`fdtd-apml_pim.exe`) generates:

- **`bbop_statistics.csv`** — execution time and energy consumption for each PIM system (bbop instruction), i.e., **SIMDRAM** and **Proteus**.

## Notes

This workload was removed from Polybench after version 4.0.